   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">You start off with Yerthi and grab Weave hyren and staff of hyrens.  Play Staff of Hyrens and Weave Hyren, and at least one other creature.  With this deck you pretty much play with what you get but for basic stratigy there are a couple points to this deck that make it a  to beat.<br>
1. Get Uwamar big, because it protects your magi and save another one of your creatures from being directly discarded from play.<br>
2. Weave Mat is very important to the deck make sure you&#39;re able to play a creature each turn and if you can&#39;t pray for tweave.<br>
3. Try to play anything that will give you card advantage, like Frusk, first.<br>
4. Always weave energy on to Weave Hyren, because his effect doesn&#39;t help him.<br>
5. Save harmony for Kesia because of her native strength ability(Spells cost 2 less to min. of 1. Can only play weave spells)<br>
6. Make them attack you, it takes a lot of advantage awa from them.<br>
I hope this helps a lot more than I first had it.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
